node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Billy Gene Is Marketing 🌐 on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 5 people and people standing.

node.text:
They say "dream big". 

Growing up my biggest "dream" never included traveling on private jets. 

So I think the idea is to dream big annually. 

Because if we're progressing our version of "big" will constantly be challenged. 

Anyways, to some people this picture is a group of guys flexing on a pj. 

To me this is me flexing my brain on the idea of what's possible. 

Geneius > Genius. 

P.S. Shit like this is only possible because of "we" not me. Shout out to everyone in this pic and then some, my brothers for life. And my girl who gave me permission to go to Vegas lol.

node.text:
Could have invested into crypto.

Could have bought penny stocks. 

Could have saved for a rainy day. 

My aunt could have had balls but then she'd be my uncle.

So I guess what I'm trying to say is...

1. Getting the city to shut down my street

And 

2. Paying a company to crane my new spa to my balcony was worth every fucking penny. 

Because I got the most underrated ROI of all-time:

Happiness! 

Cheers,  it's always impossible until somebody does it.

node.text:
"Well Warren Buffett still drives a beat up Chrysler".

Yah, fuck that noise. Happy 33rd birthday to me.

Got another lambo. Moved to the beach. Renewed our suite at the Padres.  Traveling. Speaking. Filming. Kicking it with my girls. 

Ads have now been seen 1,000,000,000 times. 

Day 60 of 75 hard, feeling like a fucking savage. 

Your boy is back. You know the vibes. Link in bio. Buy my shit. 

We just getting started.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Billy Gene Is Marketing 🌐 on December 22, 2020. May be an image of one or more people and road.

node.text:
Merry Christmas from Black Santa... 

Spent 5gs this morning buying gifts for people: 8k TV, laptops, ga+ 

Tell Black Santa what you want?

Have you ever been jealous before? 

It's something I've struggled with for my entire life...

6 or 7 years ago I went to this "internet marketing" event called Traffic and Conversion summit.

I remember watching my dude Ryan deiss on stage thinking fuck I want to be on that stage. I got so damn jealous! 

And it kept happening... Id keep going to these events and the entire time in the back of my mind I'd be thinking of ways to get in "their" shoes. 

Then I made a decision:

1. Keep sitting here feeling like a jealous insecure bitch 

Or 

2. Use that as fuel and motivation to make shit happen. 

6 years later here I am Keynoting Day 2 on the main stage. 

Thanks T&C it was an honor and a blessing but if im keeping it 100 I still got jealous. 

I got jealous because I wasn't the day 1 keynote, Arnold Schwarzenegger was lol. 

Let me be clear, I'm very aware Arnold is on a different level than me. 

But me setting what others deem as an "unrealistic" goal
Is what got me here in the first place.

Besides Arnold is 73, I'm 32 so I guess I got some time. 

Cheers to turning our weaknesses into our strengths.

node.text:

2. My driver kev  will pick you up in my Sprinter 
3. We'll head to my studio where ill feature you on my podcast 
4. All access to myself, my marketing, media, sales, and financial team for the day.
5. Well take the lambo to lunch at the University Club 
6. I'll write an email promoting you or your product to my list of almost 1,000,000 entrepreneurs. (Rev share). 
7. I'll feature you on all our social platforms.
8. Lifetime membership to GA plus 
9. Well finish the day with dinner at my penthouse and my chef will.make us w.e you want

Good luck! Start the bidding in 3...2...1...
